      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Isaiah 27:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). I will shew them the back, and not the face.—The figure is boldly anthropomorphic. The light of God’s countenance is the fulness of joy (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 6:25",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). To turn away that light was to leave the people to the darkness of their misery. What was thus done by Jehovah was but a righteous retribution on the people who had “turned their back” and “not their face” to Him (",
        "children": []
